England Beats Sri Lanka by 16 Runs to Win One-Day Cricket Series

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-09T17:41:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-09/england-beats-sri-lanka-by-16-runs-to-win-one-day-cricket-series.html
England  defeated  Sri Lanka  by 16 runs
to win their one-day cricket series 3-2.  Tim Bresnan  took three wickets as Sri Lanka was bowled out
for 252 in response to England’s 268-9 at Old Trafford in
Manchester. Angelo Mathews top-scored for Sri Lanka with 62.  Jonathan Trott  scored 72 for England, which won the toss
and batted first, while Suraj Randiv took 5-42 for the visitors.  England next plays  India  in a four-Test series beginning
July 21 at Lord’s in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  